<br>
If you want to built aggro you atk, you do dmg, you use proc, you ask a sk to cast that crap buff on you, etc.  <br>
<br>
Having taunt work like a reverse evade would suck imo.  Evade is a skill that make it absolutly trivial for a rogue to avoid aggro.<br>
<br>
I don't want taunt to be trivial.<br>
<br>
The logic is simple.  It was stated many times by people on this forum.  If by definition the warrior is the one that should be tanking because of ac/def/hp, then it should not be trivial to have the mob be on him.  It then become a concerted effort for the raid/group to make certain that the mob is on the optimum tank, in this case let's say the warrior.  In that sense, anyong stealing aggro from the tank does a disservice to the raid.  Let's avoid doing a comparaison with knights for a sec, and look at the fact that shaman can steal aggro instantly by casting slow.  Do you want shaman tanking? No, you want the warrior to tank, so it should be harder for the shaman to avoid aggro somewhat and harder for the warrior to get aggro to tank.<br>
<br>
I don't want this game to become even more trivial then it is.  <br>
<br>
I will just repeat it again, taunt work fine in pop.  having it work even more then that would make it trivial to get aggro.<br>
<br>
Thorbadin<br>
